These extensions include additional functions for modules such as Array, List, Set, and Map; immutable IntSet, IntMap, LazyList, and Queue collections; a variety of computation expressions (workflows); and "workflow collections" -- collections modules which have been adapted to work seamlessly from within workflows.

FeedPackage.Description:
DynamicPDF Core Suite brings tons of PDF creation and manipulation features into your Visual Studio application. Whether your need is to bring in an existing PDF document (for Form Filling, Form Flattening, Merging, Splitting, Adding New Pages, Stamping or Watermarking, Encrypting or Password Protecting, Text Extraction, etc.) or you want to create PDF files from scratch with an incredible depth of features (including Barcodes, Tables, Charts, Form Fields, Images, Hyperlinks, Text overflow, Lists, Custom and built-in Fonts, Document Linearization, JavaScript, Digital Signatures, PDF Tagging, PDF/A, PDF/X and so much more) DynamicPDF Core Suite has all the features you will need.
DynamicPDF Core Suite is backed by a great team of developers who maintain and are available for informative dialog about all aspects of the product. Flexible licenses (including royalty free) are available to meet all developers’ needs.
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes:
DynamicPDF Generator for .NET: ◦ Several TIFF to PDF conversion issues are fixed. ◦ Couple of PDF generation issues that are causing errors when the resulting PDF is viewed/printed in Adobe Reader are resolved.
DynamicPDF Merger for .NET: ◦ Out of memory exception while linearizing specific PDF has been resolved. ◦ Several null reference exceptions while merging PDFs have been fixed. ◦ Multiple invalid cast exceptions when merging certain PDF were resolved. ◦ PDF parsing exceptions during merging of specific PDFs has been fixed.
A license is not required for evaluation usage. But a version specific license is required for production usage.
FeedPackage.Summary: DynamicPDF Core Suite is designed for .NET developers who need PDF creation, merging, form filling, stamping, securing/encryption and much more. The API is easy to use yet contains tons of features.

DynamicPDF Viewer is a PDF viewing control you can embed in a .NET Windows Form application. Viewer is highly efficient and lightweight and can add PDF viewing to any WinForm application without relying on any third party or external resources. It uses the Foxit PDF rendering engine which is the same rendering engine that is used by the popular Foxit PDF Reader. DynamicPDF Viewer for .NET seamlessly integrates with our other DynamicPDF products allowing applications to display PDF output from any of our other DynamicPDF tools (but will work with any PDF file regardless of producer). It is compatible with PDF version v1.1 to v1.7.
This package is for x64 processor architecture.
